Thank you everyone for your input, it helps a lot. <P>The same day I posted this I got sick of Keltoi but didn&#8217;t want to go to catacombs yet, so an armsman friend of mine and I went to Cornwall. He was a little nervous about the boogies because they were orange. We were able to do them easily in my opinion, but then I was standing off to the side while he was in the face of the boogey  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> So we kept exploring and found the house where all the roman skelys are. <P>This was a great find because the sorcerers DD spell does bonus damage per hit against the skelys, plus I got three Roman Tactician Bracers and the DeathRune Robes within the three hours we played there and other stuff that I didn&#8217;t much care for like weapons and the like. <P>I also like that there is so much to fight and it is not a tight spaced over crowded place. So in my opinion I will not be going back to Keltoi. <P>Tarshishim
